node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Along the way, Kia tweaks things here and there (blanched green beans instead of canned; sautéed chicken instead of boiled) to make the recipe her own while she and her mom talk about the origins of this delicious dish with the whimsical name. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.text:
“When I think of my Afro-Latinidad and African American heritage, the culinary blessings of both of my cultures bring me the most joy. When I was growing up, my parents incorporated both of these cultures into everyday recipes, which helped me understand that the individual cultures didn’t need to exist in a vacuum” says @senseandedibility.

This batata casserole with pecan coconut topping is one of the mezclas (mixes) she’s the fondest of. Made with the batata sweet potato variety, it isn’t as sweet as the traditional sweet potato casserole and makes for a delicious vegetarian meal or holiday side dish. Tap the link in bio to get her recipe! (Image: @ambergressphotography; Food Styling: @krack513; Prop Styling: @vanessalvazquez) #thekitchn
